article.headline: New Orleans 64, North Texas 62
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Bo McCalebb hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to give New Orleans a 64-to-62 victory over North Texas on Thursday night. Ben Bell's free throw with two seconds remaining broke a 61-61 tie to give North Texas the lead. But McCalebb caught a long inbounds pass before hitting the game-winning shot as time ran out. McCalebb led New Orleans (11-13, 7-6 Sun Belt) with 25 points and 10 rebounds. Jamie McNeilly added 18 points, while James Parlow had 14, including four 3-pointers. The Privateers led 34-29 at the half, but North Texas closed the gap in the final minute on back-to-back baskets by Kendrick Davis. Quincy Williams and Keith Wooden each had 16 points for the Mean Green (16-8, 7-6). Wooden led the team with 13 rebounds, while Williams grabbed 10. Calvin Watson added 12 points.
